-{"id":"rust_proxy-cux","title":"E2E Test Infrastructure Foundation","description":"## Overview

Establish a comprehensive end-to-end testing infrastructure for rust_proxy that enables reliable, reproducible integration testing across all features.

## Strategic Value

E2E tests are essential for:
- Catching integration issues that unit tests miss
- Validating real-world behavior across component boundaries
- Providing confidence for refactoring and feature additions
- Documenting expected system behavior through executable specs
- Enabling CI/CD automation with reliable test gates

## Architecture

### Test Harness Components

```rust
// tests/common/mod.rs
pub struct TestHarness {
    /// Temporary directory for test artifacts
    pub temp_dir: TempDir,
    /// Test configuration file path
    pub config_path: PathBuf,
    /// State directory path
    pub state_dir: PathBuf,
    /// Mock proxy servers (if needed)
    pub mock_proxies: Vec<MockProxy>,
    /// The daemon process handle
    pub daemon: Option<DaemonHandle>,
}

impl TestHarness {
    pub async fn new() -> Self { ... }
    pub async fn with_config(config: &str) -> Self { ... }
    pub async fn start_daemon(&mut self) -> Result<()> { ... }
    pub async fn stop_daemon(&mut self) -> Result<()> { ... }
    pub fn run_command(&self, args: &[&str]) -> CommandResult { ... }
    pub async fn cleanup(self) { ... }
}
```

### Mock Proxy Server

```rust
pub struct MockProxy {
    pub port: u16,
    pub addr: SocketAddr,
    /// Configurable behavior
    pub behavior: MockBehavior,
    /// Request log for assertions
    pub requests: Arc<Mutex<Vec<MockRequest>>>,
}

pub enum MockBehavior {
    /// Always succeed with configurable latency
    Healthy { latency_ms: u64 },
    /// Always fail with specific error
    Failing { error: MockError },
    /// Succeed N times then fail
    FailAfter { successes: u32, error: MockError },
    /// Random failures at given rate
    Flaky { failure_rate: f64 },
    /// Custom handler
    Custom(Box<dyn Fn(&MockRequest) -> MockResponse>),
}
```

### Test Logging Infrastructure

```rust
/// Detailed test logging for debugging failures
pub struct TestLogger {
    log_path: PathBuf,
    verbosity: LogVerbosity,
}

impl TestLogger {
    /// Log test phase transitions
    pub fn phase(&self, name: &str) { ... }
    /// Log command execution with output
    pub fn command(&self, cmd: &str, output: &CommandResult) { ... }
    /// Log assertion details
    pub fn assertion(&self, name: &str, expected: &str, actual: &str) { ... }
    /// Capture daemon logs during test
    pub fn daemon_logs(&self) -> String { ... }
}
```

### Test Fixture Generators

```rust
pub fn minimal_config() -> String { ... }
pub fn multi_proxy_config(count: usize) -> String { ... }
pub fn config_with_health_check(interval_secs: u64) -> String { ... }
pub fn config_with_failover() -> String { ... }
```

## Directory Structure

```
tests/
├── common/
│   ├── mod.rs          # Test harness and utilities
│   ├── mock_proxy.rs   # Mock proxy server implementation
│   ├── fixtures.rs     # Config and data fixtures
│   └── assertions.rs   # Custom assertion helpers
├── e2e/
│   ├── basic_operations.rs
│   ├── health_check.rs
│   ├── failover.rs
│   ├── metrics.rs      # When metrics feature implemented
│   └── ...
└── integration/
    ├── cli_commands.rs
    └── config_parsing.rs
```

## Key Testing Patterns

### 1. Daemon Lifecycle Test
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_daemon_start_stop() {
    let mut harness = TestHarness::new().await;

    harness.start_daemon().await.expect("daemon should start");
    assert!(harness.daemon_is_running());

    harness.stop_daemon().await.expect("daemon should stop");
    assert!(!harness.daemon_is_running());
}
```

### 2. Health Check Test with Mock
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_health_check_marks_unhealthy() {
    let mut harness = TestHarness::new().await;
    let mock = harness.add_mock_proxy(MockBehavior::Failing {
        error: MockError::ConnectionRefused
    }).await;

    harness.start_daemon().await.unwrap();

    // Wait for health check cycle
    tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(5)).await;

    let status = harness.run_command(&["status", "--json"]);
    let json: Value = serde_json::from_str(&status.stdout).unwrap();

    assert_eq!(json["proxies"][&mock.id]["health"], "unhealthy");
}
```

### 3. Failover Test
```rust
#[tokio::test]
async fn test_automatic_failover() {
    let mut harness = TestHarness::with_config(r#"
        [settings]
        auto_failover = true
        consecutive_failures_threshold = 2

        [[proxies]]
        id = "primary"
        url = "http://localhost:MOCK1_PORT"
        priority = 1

        [[proxies]]
        id = "secondary"
        url = "http://localhost:MOCK2_PORT"
        priority = 2
    "#).await;

    let primary = harness.add_mock_proxy(MockBehavior::FailAfter {
        successes: 2,
        error: MockError::Timeout
    }).await;
    let secondary = harness.add_mock_proxy(MockBehavior::Healthy {
        latency_ms: 50
    }).await;

    harness.start_daemon().await.unwrap();

    // Wait for failover
    tokio::time::sleep(Duration::from_secs(10)).await;

    let status = harness.run_command(&["status", "--json"]);
    assert!(status.stdout.contains("\"effective_proxy\": \"secondary\""));
}
```

## Logging Requirements

Every E2E test MUST:
1. Log test phase transitions (setup, execute, verify, teardown)
2. Capture full command output (stdout + stderr)
3. Record daemon logs during test
4. Log assertion details on failure
5. Preserve logs on test failure for debugging

## CI Integration

Tests should be runnable via:
```bash
# All E2E tests
cargo test --test e2e

# Specific feature tests
cargo test --test e2e health_check

# With verbose logging
RUST_LOG=debug cargo test --test e2e -- --nocapture
```

## Success Criteria

- Test harness can start/stop daemon reliably
- Mock proxy server supports all needed behaviors
- Tests are isolated (no shared state between tests)
- Clear logging on test failure
- Tests complete in reasonable time (<60s each)
- All tests pass in CI environment","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T14:47:50.785175185-05:00","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T16:55:25.129811968-05:00"}
